<TITLE> 2 PCJSS men dead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, May 15 (bdnews24.com)  Two people were killed in an ambush at Chhoto Panchharri under Jurachhari upazila at Rangamati on Saturday, police said. Two others were also shot. The administration, although confirmed the killing, could not say anything about the bodies and those injured. The dead, identified by the locals as Rupayan Chakma alias Tapan, 27, and Shohag Chakma, 22, were members of Parbattya Chattagram Jana Shanghati Shamiti (PCJSS), supporters of the Peace Accord. Two othersLakshmi Chandra Chakma, 27, and Purna Chandra Chakma, 35 were also shot in the incident. Locals said that the four members of PCJSS went to Chhoto Paanchhari from Aimchhora of Barkal upazila Saturday morning. Then they were attacked by members of the United People's Democratic Front (UPDF). Upon receiving information of the incident police and military forces went to the scene. But they found no bodies, said the officer in charge of Jurachhari Police Station, Md Rafiq. Rafiq said the villagers had told them about hearing shots. When contacted, UNO of Jurachhari, Abu Ali Md Sajjad, said that they had information of two persons being killed. Necessary measures were undertaken to keep the situation under control, he added. District police superintendent Masudul Hasan confirmed the deaths. "We've heard of the killing of two PCJSS members." However, Sajib Chakma, central assistant information and publicity secretary of PCJSS, told bdnews24.com: "We had heard that two were killed and two wounded in the incident." But he could not confirm which group they belonged to. bdnews
